# Xcode Cloud Environment Variables
# These MUST be configured in App Store Connect for iOS builds to work

## Setup Instructions:

### Step 1: Access Xcode Cloud Settings
1. Go to https://appstoreconnect.apple.com
2. Select your app (Welp!)
3. Click "Xcode Cloud" in the left sidebar
4. Select your workflow (or create one)
5. Click "Edit Workflow"

### Step 2: Add Environment Variables
1. Go to the "Environment" tab
2. Scroll to "Environment Variables" section
3. Click "+ Add Environment Variable"
4. Add each variable below:
   - Name: (copy the variable name exactly)
   - Value: (copy the value)
   - ☑️ Check "Secret" for security (recommended for keys)

### Step 3: Verify Variables Are Set
After adding variables, the build script will validate them automatically.
Check the build logs for:
  ✓ VITE_SUPABASE_URL is set
  ✓ VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY is set

